Refere:- https://docs.conda.io/projects/conda/en/latest/user-guide/tasks/manage-environments.html#create-env-file-manually
         https://salishsea-meopar-docs.readthedocs.io/en/latest/work_env/porting_to_python3.html


Create env:-
    conda create -n mypython3 python=3

Active ENV:-
    conda activate mypython3
    
To get all the goodies (e.g. Jupyter Notebook, NumPy, matplotlib) you can install Anaconda, which will auto-magically use Python 3.
    conda install anaconda
    
and then our additional install, netcdf4-python

    conda install netcdf4
